parameters:
Kru: "Umi... I'm sorry about earlier. Even if it wasn't on purpose, I feel
like I did something wrong."

Umi: "Hmm... It's not that I'm angry. It's just... I'm feeling a bit
frustrated..."
Kru: "Then... close your eyes and hold out your hands..."
Umi: "What! What did you give me?!"
Kru: "It's... It's okay... It's not something scary."
Umi: "If it's something scary... Umi will really get angry..."
Kru: "It's fine. Now, open your eyes!"
Kru: "I just picked them. Please cheer up with this."
Kru: "Uh, Umi-san... I'm sorry... Are you angry?"
Umi: "...Beautiful... It's the first time I've received a bouquet..."

Umi: "In the past, Kaka said that Toto gave her one... She was so happy,
she made it into a pressed flower and used it as a bookmark..."
Kru: "Heh, so that happened. That's a nice memory."
Umi: "Yeah... Kaka treasured that bookmark a lot..."
Kru: "I see... Your mother must have really loved your father."
Umi: "And then... Umi thought that someday she would receive one too..."
Kru: "Oh! So that 'someday' was today, huh?"
Kru: "Right? Sometimes things other than meat are nice too, right?"
Kru: (Just now... Umi said... thank you...)

Kru: (This girl can say thank you... I was mistaken to think she was a bad
kid because of her rough speech.)

Kru: "That's right... She took care of me for a whole month... She's a good
kid. She even remembers her late mother's words..."
Umi: "But... I still haven't forgiven you... so listen to my request."
Umi: "Carry this pig. It's too heavy for Umi."

Umi: "Umi is delicate. If you don't carry it, I'll tell the whole village
that you groped my breasts."
Kru: "No way! Please don't do that!"

Kru: "Umi... You carried this pig all the way here, right? Isn't this
'delicate' thing a lie?"

Umi: "It's different. Umi is delicate. Can't carry it. The pig walked here
on its own."
Umi: "Do your best! Don't give up!"
